result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (3rd) and Operating w/ PAC (3rd). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (3rd) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (3rd) was dismissed by the court.

  • Timothy Richard Mckinney was found guilty of OWI (3rd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).
  • Timothy Richard Mckinney was found guilty of Vehicle Operator Flee/Elude Officer, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(3).

For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
9:45 a.m.  Defendant appeared in court with Atty Jon Wilsnack.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty Wilsnack recites agreement - defendant will plea to counts 1 & 2 and counts 3 & 4 will be dismissed.  Statement by DA.  Atty Wilsnack concurs.  Defendant concurs.  

Court instructs the defendant regarding his right to a preliminary examination.  Defendant waives his right to a preliminary examination.  Court accepts the waiver of the prelim and binds the defendant over for trial.  State files an information with the court.  Attorney Wilsnack and defendant acknowledge receipt of the information and waives any reading.  Atty Wilsnack enters a plea of NO CONTEST to counts 1 & 2 on behalf of the defendant.  

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.  Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions.

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST to counts 1 & 2.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on counts 1 & 2.  Court orders counts 3 & 4 be dismissed.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  Sentencing statement by DA.  Sentencing statement by Atty Wilsnack.  Statement by the defendant.

No objection by DA to return the personal property to the defendant from the seized vehicle.

Court sentences the defendant to:

Count 1 (OWI-3rd)

-60 days jail with huber and to commence immediately.
-$600 fine plus costs
-DL revocation for 24 months
-IID for 24 months
-AODA

Count 2

Sentence Withheld and places the defendant on probation for a period of one year.

CONDITIONS:

-court costs
-  Defendant is to abide by all rules and recommendations of the supervising agent.
-  Defendant is to maintain absolute sobriety - not to possess or consume any alcohol, illegal drugs or prescription drugs without a valid prescription.

Court remands the defendant to the custody of the Green Lake County Sheriff's Department.  Court will allow the return of the personal property from the seized vehicle.  Atty Wilsnack to submit an order.

Court adjourned at 10:01 a.m.
Plea/sentencing hearing on January 6, 2015 at 09:00 am.
